Tanzania giants Simba SC have been drawn against South Africa's Orlando Pirates in the quarter-finals of the CAF Confederation Cup. Best known as ‘Wekundu wa Msimba’ the Msimbazi based club sailed through CAF Confederation Cup quarter-finals after beating USGN 4-0 in a final match of Group D and secured second position with 10 points. According to draws conducted in Cairo on Tuesday, Pyramids have been paired against TP Mazembe. Simba’s opponents in Group D RS Berkane have been drawn to Al Masry while Al Ittihad from Libya will face their fellow opponent from Tripoli, Ahly Tripoli. According to the timetable, Simba SC will face Pirates in the first leg in Dar es Salaam on 17th April, 2022 while the return leg will be played at Orland Stadium in Johannesburg, South Africa